            ],
            "weighting": "<dd>16%</dd>",
            "due_date": "<dd><p>Quiz 1 7/08/2026 4:00 pm</p>\n<p>Quiz 2 21/08/2026 4:00 pm</p>\n<p>Quiz 3 28/08/2026 4:00 pm</p>\n<p>Quiz 4 4/09/2026 4:00 pm</p>\n<p>Quiz 5 11/09/2026 4:00 pm</p>\n<p>Quiz 6 18/09/2026 4:00 pm</p>\n<p>Quiz 7 25/09/2026 4:00 pm</p>\n<p>Quiz 8 16/10/2026 4:00 pm</p>\n<p>Quiz 9 23/10/2026 4:00 pm</p>\n<p>Quiz 10 30/10/2026 4:00 pm</p>\n<p>\n</p><p>Individual questions are due by 4:00 pm on Fridays. Collaborative questions are due by the end of your allocated applied class.</p></dd>",
            "learning_objectives": "L02, L05, L06",
            "mode": "Activity/ Performance, Written",
            "category": "Participation/ Student contribution, Quiz, Tutorial/ Problem Set",
            "task_description": "<div class=\"collapsible collapsible--text\">\n<p>In each of the ten weeks that there is an applied classes there will be a quiz to complete online. Each quiz will involve 10 questions:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Five questions are <strong>individual questions.</strong> These questions will open at 8:00 am on Monday and close at 4:00 pm on Friday. Most will involve analysing data using <strong>RStudio</strong> and completing these will be an important opportunity to learn the details of working with RStudio. You are encouraged to discuss these questions using the <strong>Ed</strong> Discussion Board.</li>\n<li>Five questions are <strong>collaborative questions</strong>. These questions will be completed during your allocated applied class.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Your best eight quiz marks will each count 2% towards your overall grade (for a maximum of 16%).</p>\n<button class=\"collapsible__toggle\">\n<span class=\"collapsible__open link--icon icon--standard--arrow-down-1\">Read full task description</span>\n<span class=\"collapsible__close link--icon icon--standard--arrow-up-1\">Hide full task description</span>\n</button>\n</div>",
            "submission_guidelines": "<p>Complete via Blackboard.</p>",
            "deferral_or_extension": "<p>You may be able to <a href=\"https://my.uq.edu.au/information-and-services/manage-my-program/exams-and-assessment/applying-assessment-extension\">apply for an extension</a>.</p>",
            "late_submission": "<p>You will receive a mark of 0 if this assessment is <a href=\"https://policies.uq.edu.au/document/view-current.php?id=184\">submitted late</a>.</p>",
            "additional_info": "<p>You may be able to <a href=\"https://my.uq.edu.au/information-and-services/manage-my-program/exams-and-assessment/applying-assessment-extension\">apply for an extension</a>.</p>"
        },
        {
            "assessment_detail_section_id": "assessment-detail-1",
            "assessment_title": "Paper Review",
            "special_indicators": [
                {
                    "special_indicators_class": "icon--standard--alert-triangle icon-text--small",
                    "special_indicator_text": "Hurdle"
                },
                {
                    "special_indicators_class": "icon--education--bookmarks-document icon-text--small",
                    "special_indicator_text": "Identity Verified"
                },
                {
                    "special_indicators_class": "icon--how-youll-learn--multiple-circle-1 icon-text--small",
                    "special_indicator_text": "In-person"
                }
            ],
            "weighting": "<dd>14%</dd>",
            "due_date": "<dd><p> 28/08/2026 4:00 pm</p></dd>",
            "learning_objectives": "L01, L02, L03, L04",
            "mode": "Written",
            "category": "Essay/ Critique",
            "task_description": "<div class=\"collapsible collapsible--text\">\n<p>The Paper Review involves finding a scientific paper of interest to you through the library. You can choose any paper you like as long as it has a <em>p</em>-value and a DOI and was published no earlier than 2023. Each paper can only be reviewed by one group so once you have your paper you must register it on Blackboard.</p>\n<p>The Paper Review consists of two components namely the statistics component and the ethics component. You will need to provide a brief summary of the statistical inference under the statistics component and an essay discussing the ethical issues involved in the study under the ethics component. See Blackboard for examples.</p>\n<p>The review is submitted using a form on Blackboard. The maximum word limits are 250 words for the statistics component and 500 words for the ethics component.</p>\n<p>The Paper Review may be completed in groups of up to three students. Use the tools on Blackboard if you want to form a group. Groups must be formed by the due date.</p>\n<button class=\"collapsible__toggle\">\n<span class=\"collapsible__open link--icon icon--standard--arrow-down-1\">Read full task description</span>\n<span class=\"collapsible__close link--icon icon--standard--arrow-up-1\">Hide full task description</span>\n</button>\n</div>",
            "submission_guidelines": "<p>Complete via Blackboard</p>",
            "deferral_or_extension": "<p>You may be able to <a href=\"https://my.uq.edu.au/information-and-services/manage-my-program/exams-and-assessment/applying-assessment-extension\">apply for an extension</a>.</p>",
            "late_submission": "<p>A <a href=\"https://policies.uq.edu.au/document/view-current.php?id=184\">penalty</a> of 10% of the maximum possible mark will be deducted per 24 hours from time submission is due for up to 7 days. After 7 days, you will receive a mark of 0.</p>",
            "additional_info": "<p>You may be able to <a href=\"https://my.uq.edu.au/information-and-services/manage-my-program/exams-and-assessment/applying-assessment-extension\">apply for an extension</a>.</p>"
        },
