            "weighting": "<dd>20%</dd>",
            "due_date": "<dd><p> 23/10/2026 4:00 pm</p></dd>",
            "learning_objectives": "L02, L06, L07",
            "mode": "Product/ Artefact/ Multimedia",
            "category": "Presentation, Project",
            "task_description": "<div class=\"collapsible collapsible--text\">\n<p>For the Research Project you will design a study, carry it out with a population of virtual subjects to collect your data, and then analyse the results and present them in the form of a presentation, as would be given at a scientific conference. Your presentation will be in the form of a video of between 5 to 6 minutes in length and featuring each person in the group talking to camera (separately or together). Further information about creating your video is provided on Blackboard.</p>\n<p>The research project may be completed individually or in groups of up to three students.</p>\n<p>Generative Artificial Intelligence (AI) may be used to support students in brainstorming their research topic and developing their study design, addressing the first two criteria of this assessment task. You are encouraged to complete all the data analysis and interpretation yourself (Criteria 3 - 6), since these are important skills that you will need for the End of Semester Examination.</p>\n<button class=\"collapsible__toggle\">\n<span class=\"collapsible__open link--icon icon--standard--arrow-down-1\">Read full task description</span>\n<span class=\"collapsible__close link--icon icon--standard--arrow-up-1\">Hide full task description</span>\n</button>\n</div>",
            "submission_guidelines": "<p>Submit via Blackboard.</p>",
            "deferral_or_extension": "<p>You may be able to <a href=\"https://my.uq.edu.au/information-and-services/manage-my-program/exams-and-assessment/applying-assessment-extension\">apply for an extension</a>.</p>",
            "late_submission": "<p>A <a href=\"https://policies.uq.edu.au/document/view-current.php?id=184\">penalty</a> of 10% of the maximum possible mark will be deducted per 24 hours from time submission is due for up to 7 days. After 7 days, you will receive a mark of 0.</p>",
            "additional_info": "<p>You may be able to <a href=\"https://my.uq.edu.au/information-and-services/manage-my-program/exams-and-assessment/applying-assessment-extension\">apply for an extension</a>.</p>"
